### HYMN XXVI

#### To Affliction

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0602601">1</span></span>Let me go
free, O Misery: do thou, the mighty, pity us.  
  Set me uninjured in the world of happiness, O Misery.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0602602">2</span></span>From thee,
from thee who fliest not from us, O Misery, we fly.  
  Then at the turning of the paths let Misery fall on someone else.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0602603">3</span></span>May the
immortal, thousand eyed, dwell otherwhere apart from  
   us.  
  Let him afflict the man we hate: smite only him who is our foe.

